JD - 1 : 

Job Summary:
• This role requires a strategic thinker with extensive experience in the pharmaceutical industry, capable of navigating complex General Administration, Liasoning and fostering a positive workplace culture.
• The ideal candidate will be adept at aligning Administrative strategies with business objectives, ensuring compliance with standards, and promoting effective communication across the organization.
• Aligning and Cascading with Corporate Administration business strategies and ensuring Statutory compliances.

Qualifications:
• Masters degree in Business Administration or relevant Qualification (MBA/PG).
• Minimum of 20+ years of progressive Administration experience, with at least 15 years in a leadership role within the pharmaceutical industry.
• Extensive experience in Facility Management and working with Industrial Relations.
• Proven track record in developing and implementing Administrative strategies that align with business objectives.
• Excellent negotiation, conflict resolution, and interpersonal skills.
• Superior communication skills, both verbal and written.
• Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced and dynamic environment.
• Strong leadership and team management skills.

Preferred Skills:
• Knowledge of the latest Administration trends and best practices.
• Public speaking and media handling skills.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JD - 2 : 

Key Responsibilities
• Manage administration and facility operations across all factory units and the head office.
• Supervise housekeeping, security, maintenance, utilities, and transport services.
• Maintain and renew statutory, social, ethical, and technical compliance records (BSCI, SEDEX, ISO, CTPAT, etc.).
• Coordinate and prepare for buyer, third-party, and internal factory audits.
• Liaise with government departments, consultants, and certifying agencies for license renewals and inspections.
• Support HR and Operations teams with logistics, documentation, and staff facility management.
• Track audit corrective actions and ensure timely compliance closures.
• Maintain MIS and reporting systems for administrative and compliance functions.

Qualifications & Skills
• Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Management, or related field (Master’s preferred).
• 8–12 years of experience in administration and compliance within a manufacturing or export setup.
• Familiarity with factory compliance standards (BSCI, SEDEX, ISO, WRAP, etc.).
• Strong organizational, coordination, and problem-solving skills.
• Proficiency in MS Office and digital documentation systems.
• Ability to manage multi-site operations effectively.

Key Attributes
• Integrity, discipline, and attention to detail.
• Strong follow-up and accountability.
• Hands-on approach with the ability to manage multiple priorities.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JD - 3 : 

Key Responsibilities:
- Manage the GM's calendar, schedule appointments, and coordinate meetings.
- Make travel arrangements, book flights, and hotels.
- Prepare and coordinate presentations, reports, and documents.
- Handle incoming and outgoing correspondence, emails, and phone calls.
- Prioritize tasks, manage multiple projects, and meet deadlines.
- Maintain accurate records, files, and databases.
- Maintain confidentiality on sensitive matters and handle information with discretion.
- Assist the GM with special projects, events, and initiatives.

Qualifications Required:
- Education: Any Graduate.
- Experience: 3+ years as an Executive Assistant or Administrative Assistant.
- Skills: Excellent communication, organizational, and time management skills; Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook); Ability to maintain confidentiality and handle sensitive information.
- Personal Qualities: Friendly, approachable, and professional demeanor; Ability to work independently and as part of a team.

