JD - 4 : 

Skills/Qualifications:
• Educational Background:
• Bachelor's degree in Business Administration, Management, Engineering, or a related field (other backgrounds are also welcome to apply)
• Experience:
• Minimum of 5-8 years of experience in a managerial role within the inspection services industry, international trading company or a related sector in Industries like Renewable Energy, Industrial Equipmetn, Chemical materials. TIC industry will be preferred.
• Proven track record of successfully managing operations and leading teams in a multinational environment.

Skills:
• Strong leadership and team management skills, with the ability to inspire and motivate others.
• Excellent financial acumen, with experience in budgeting, financial analysis, and strategic planning.
• Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to build strong relationships with clients, partners, and stakeholders.
• Strategic thinking and problem-solving abilities, with a proactive approach to addressing challenges.
• Fluency in English, both written and verbal, is required.
• Personal Attributes:
• High level of integrity and professionalism.
• Ability to work under pressure and manage multiple priorities.
• Strong cultural awareness and adaptability in a diverse working environment.

Compensation: Negotiable, with a competitive base salary and performance incentives.


